{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_01NJVrX3DY6Ex8mX7ZkESnaK","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I understand the issues:\n\n1. **R-001**: `resolve_fmt_mode()` correctly coerces `FMT_MODE` to `check` in CI. But on line 232, `fix_enabled` checks `RUN_FIX == \"1\" || FMT_MODE == \"fix\"`. Since CI coerces FMT_MODE to \"check\", the `FMT_MODE == \"fix\"` part is fine. BUT `RUN_FIX == \"1\"` is still true! So `fix_enabled=1` even in CI. The fix: after `resolve_fmt_mode`, also coerce `RUN_FIX=0` in CI, or change `fix_enabled` to only check `FMT_MODE == \"fix\"`.\n   \n   The cleanest approach is to make `fix_enabled` depend solely on `FMT_MODE` after resolution, since `resolve_fmt_mode` already handles the `RUN_FIX` logic for local auto mode. This way `fix_enabled` just checks if `FMT_MODE` is \"fix\".\n\n2. **R-002**: Add `tests/sql-agent/clean-dialect/` fixture.\n\n3. **R-003**: See if I can trim the script down a bit.\n\nNow I'm going to implement these fixes.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":3642,"cache_read_input_tokens":28757,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":3642},"output_tokens":8,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"68883e57-9b47-43a2-a1be-d2340c19f997","uuid":"e133c934-173e-4f5f-9b5f-cc4bbae154e1"}
